Package: ggcpb
Title: CPB House-Style Plotting on a ggplot2 Backend
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("CPB Netherlands Bureau for Economic Policy Analysis", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
           email = "j.j.klingen@cpb.nl")
    )
Description: A composable ggplot2 extension encoding the CPB (Centraal
    Planbureau) house plotting style: a theme, categorical and
    sequential colour palettes and scales, Dutch-locale number
    formatters, a figure export helper with CPB page-width presets,
    and a thin layer of high-level wrapper functions for the most
    common chart types used in CPB publications. The wrapper layer
    returns real 'ggplot' objects that can be extended further with
    the usual '+' syntax.
